Fragments X is unrelated to skin lesions and is excluded. EDS typically presents with generalized dermal fibromas and scaling, which is not fully described here. While NF II fits the multifocal neurofibromas and spinal involvement, the escalation of lesions across multiple areas aligns with its presentation. The tan-brown patches may be pigmented and part of its clinical picture.

